original: Johnsson, Vera Helena Maria, prakt, läkare, Göteborg, f. 27/10/96 i Gbg av folksk:lär. Gustav Adolf J. o. Lovisa Jonsson. — Stud:ex. i Gbg 16, folksk :lär :ex. där 17, med. kand. i Lund 21, med, lic. i StHm 26. Assist :läk. v. Saklgr. sjukh. med. avd. 25-26 o. två mån. 27, e. läk. v. kir. avd. där 26-27, vik. aman. v. med. avd. där tre mån. somm. 27, e. läk. där 27-28, aman. 29-31 o. andre läk. 31-36, prakt. läk. i Gbg sed. 36, skol-läk. v. Gbgs prakt, mellansk. f. f’l. sed. 37.
translated: Johnsson, Vera Helena Maria, nurse, physician, Gothenburg, b. 27/10/96 in Gothenburg to elementary school teacher Gustav Adolf J. and Lovisa Jonsson. - High school diploma in Gothenburg in 1916, elementary school teaching diploma there in 1917, Bachelor of Medicine in Lund in 1921, Medical Licentiate in Stockholm in 1926. Assistant physician at Sachsska Hospital medical department from 1925-26 and for two months in 1927, resident physician at the surgical department there from 1926-27, substitute resident at medical department for three months in summer 1927, and resident physician there from 1927-28. Amanuensis from 1929-31 and second physician from 1931-36. Practical physician in Gothenburg since 1936 and school physician at Gothenburg's Practical Intermediate School since 1937. Vera married but the name of her spouse is not given in the biography.
